 :tx/rationale "DS-RECOVERY: Crash recovery — checkpoint + WAL replay + .edn regeneration. PROTOCOL: On daemon start: (1) Check for checkpoint file (.braid/.cache/checkpoint.bin). If exists: deserialize Store (O(1), same as current store.bin load). Record checkpoint LSN (WAL byte offset at checkpoint time). (2) Check for WAL file (.braid/wal.bin). If exists and has entries past checkpoint LSN: read entries from LSN to end of valid chain (CRC + chain hash validated). Apply each entry's datoms to Store. (3) For each WAL entry without a corresponding .edn file: generate the .edn file (regenerate git-tracked state). (4) Store is now fully recovered — all durable transactions (WAL fsynced) are in memory and on disk as .edn. INVARIANT: After recovery, Store = fold(all .edn files) = fold(checkpoint + WAL delta). This is INV-STORE-020 maintained through crash. EDGE CASES: (a) WAL truncated mid-entry: chain hash detects exact truncation point. Entries after truncation are lost (they were never fsynced — client was not notified of durability). (b) Checkpoint corrupt: fall back to full .edn rebuild (existing load_store path). (c) Both corrupt: .edn files are the ultimate source of truth (git-tracked). Full rebuild from .edn is always possible. THREE LEVELS OF RECOVERY: Fast (checkpoint + WAL delta, O(1) + O(k)). Medium (checkpoint + full .edn delta, O(1) + O(F)). Slow (full .edn rebuild, O(F) — current behavior)."
